title: PPPP’s Farrukh Ahmad wins PS- 24 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Pakistan People’s Party Parliamentarians’ (PPPP) Syed Farrukh Ahmad Shah has won the Sindh Assembly election from PS-24, Sukkur-III by securing 41,235 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Mubin Ahmad of the Independent, who bagged votes 19,622.
Overall voters’ turn-out remained 36.82 %.
